      "span_text": "The Until recently, only three methods for the assay of rabies virus were available: titration of infectivity in animals, plaque assay in cell cultures [CITATION_1] , and complement fixation (CF). The latter method (24) measures both infectious virus and all noninfectious viral antigens. In 1968, Halonen et al. [CITATION_2] reported that rabies virus exhibits hemagglutinating activity (HA)."
